    "scale_info": {
      "name": "Sickle Cell Disease Pain Location Body Map - Adult",
      "code": "PX860601",
      "abbreviation": "PX860601",
      "description": "The Sickle Cell Disease Pain Location Body Map - Adult protocol is one question from a wider self-administered pain diary that is completed daily. This protocol is used to record the previous days level of sickle cell disease (SCD)-related pain. Additionally, the wider Sickle Cell Pain Diary capture",
